cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the problem of salient object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the relationship between where people look in scenes and what they choose as the most salient object, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper proposes a new dataset and a baseline model for salient object detection, which involves machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) subfields.
